Tidal bores are a rare natural phenomenon in which an incoming tide creates a wave of water that travels up along a river or narrow bay, causing water to flow against the current. 🌊

Video by Xiao Ligun, Via @oddlymesmerising

Explore. Share. Inspire: #earthfocus
